 Lampard brace in Chelsea win

 Liverpools John Arne Riise on Saturday. (Reuters) 

London: Champions Chelsea hit the top for the first time this season when a second-half Frank Lampard double earned them a 2-0 victory at local rivals Fulham in the Premier League on Saturday. 

England midfielder Lampard took his seasons tally to four with a 73rd-minute penalty and right-foot finish seven minutes later. 

Liverpool and Arsenal, both recovering from poor starts, began to show the kind of form to challenge Chelsea for the title with emphatic 3-0 home wins. 

Dutchman Dirk Kuyt struck at Anfield as Liverpool brushed Tottenham Hotspur aside in a rampant second half. Chile winger Mark Gonzalez opened the scoring and John Arne Riises thunderbolt condemned Spurs to their fourth defeat in six matches. 

Arsenals wait for a first league victory at their new Emirates Stadium ended with victory over Sheffield United, French duo William Gallas and Thierry Henry both on target.Aston Villa climbed to fourth place with a 2-0 home victory over Charlton Athletic. (Reuters) 




